data.name: Black Bean and Avocado Wrap
data.quickTastyDescription: A refreshing, protein-packed wrap filled with black beans, creamy avocado, and a hint of lime, perfect for a quick meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Lay the whole wheat tortilla flat on a clean surface.
In the center of the tortilla, layer the spinach leaves, followed by black beans, corn, cherry tomatoes, and avocado slices.
Drizzle lime juice over the top and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling, then roll it up tightly from the bottom to the top.
Serve immediately or wrap in foil for an on-the-go meal.
data.modifiersForBase: Add corn and tomatoes for extra flavor and nutrients.
